{"pagelen": 100, "values": [{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/302/comments/2628177.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/302#comment-2628177"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/302.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 302, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add signal whenever sim time is updated"}, "content": {"raw": "The plugin can listen to the world update signal, and set the ros time based by querying the world sim time.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>The plugin can listen to the world update signal, and set the ros time based by querying the world sim time.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2012-12-14T16:08:28.223912+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0/ca24bb11-4787-4b14-a20d-d91835e9bde2/128"}}, "nickname": "Nathan Koenig", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:095b1e12-74ed-4e20-b44f-2f0745b616e0"}, "updated_on": "2012-12-14T16:08:55.458773+00:00", "type": "issue_comment", "id": 2628177}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/302/comments/2628477.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/302#comment-2628477"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/302.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 302, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add signal whenever sim time is updated"}, "content": {"raw": "the problem we have seen is that most controller will have their own process or thread, though the model plugin might be connected to either WorldUpdateStart or WorldUpdateEnd, but the actual sim time update happens somewhere in the middle of the two.  There is then a race condition for the sim time value between when the model plugin updates and when the controller thread/process updates.   This race condition induces a time step size jitter in time offset between stamped state time produced at the model plugin level and the sim time when the controller actually receives the state update.\n\nHope that makes sense.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>the problem we have seen is that most controller will have their own process or thread, though the model plugin might be connected to either WorldUpdateStart or WorldUpdateEnd, but the actual sim time update happens somewhere in the middle of the two.  There is then a race condition for the sim time value between when the model plugin updates and when the controller thread/process updates.   This race condition induces a time step size jitter in time offset between stamped state time produced at the model plugin level and the sim time when the controller actually receives the state update.</p>\n<p>Hope that makes sense.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2012-12-14T16:51:24.492440+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "John Hsu", "uuid": "{0a186eae-abf0-4514-a951-23db5eccc286}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B0a186eae-abf0-4514-a951-23db5eccc286%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B0a186eae-abf0-4514-a951-23db5eccc286%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "https://avatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.net/557058:f3968cd3-4910-4384-8349-482a6c7889ec/5445ce6e-6273-47f0-84eb-621c86ca11cb/128"}}, "nickname": "hsu", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:f3968cd3-4910-4384-8349-482a6c7889ec"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 2628477}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/302/comments/2629545.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/302#comment-2629545"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/302.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 302, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add signal whenever sim time is updated"}, "content": {"raw": "Another aspect to keep in mind is the Reset button on the time control panel which causes [World::ResetTime](#!/osrf/gazebo/src/b0ba09e25d3c66e07d267d66e1a0b7ebe215beb4/gazebo/physics/World.cc?at=default#cl-713) to be invoked. This button resets sim time to zero without sending any signals to downstream controllers. If we want to support ResetTime functionality, we would need the sim time update signal to handle time resets. Alternatively we could disable the Reset button on the time control panel.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Another aspect to keep in mind is the Reset button on the time control panel which causes <a data-is-external-link=\"true\" href=\"#!/osrf/gazebo/src/b0ba09e25d3c66e07d267d66e1a0b7ebe215beb4/gazebo/physics/World.cc?at=default#cl-713\" rel=\"nofollow\">World::ResetTime</a> to be invoked. This button resets sim time to zero without sending any signals to downstream controllers. If we want to support ResetTime functionality, we would need the sim time update signal to handle time resets. Alternatively we could disable the Reset button on the time control panel.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2012-12-14T19:01:09.702342+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Steve Peters", "uuid": "{2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7B2ccfed09-18b8-4921-8d58-15ef01092802%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/secure.gravatar.com/avatar/1fb4816dad9e68337d3096f750951f6cd=httpsavatar-management--avatars.us-west-2.prod.public.atl-paas.netinitialsSP-1.png"}}, "nickname": "Steven Peters", "type": "user", "account_id": "557058:5de38267-b118-494c-aa76-4fab35448816"}, "updated_on": null, "type": "issue_comment", "id": 2629545}, {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/302/comments/3212488.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo/issues/302#comment-3212488"}}, "issue": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo/issues/302.json"}}, "type": "issue", "id": 302, "repository": {"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/osrf/gazebo.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/osrf/gazebo"}, "avatar": {"href": "data/bytebucket.org/ravatar/{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}ts=1694483"}}, "type": "repository", "name": "gazebo", "full_name": "osrf/gazebo", "uuid": "{51a0cd5d-8697-4eb1-8b08-e919ee881e1c}"}, "title": "add signal whenever sim time is updated"}, "content": {"raw": "Until 2.0", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Until 2.0</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2013-02-22T15:46:16.241568+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Nate Koenig", "uuid": "{c862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb}", "links": {"self": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/users/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D"}, "html": {"href": "https://bitbucket.org/%7Bc862cdd9-fcc8-4419-9fc7-e20db14b8fcb%7D/"}, "avatar": {"href": "h